---
import GeneExplorer from '../components/GeneExplorer'
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro'
---

<Base
  title="JBrowse integration — JBrowseMSA"
  description="Type any human gene and get a connected JBrowse session: a collapsed-intron gene view, its 100-way protein alignment, and the AlphaFold structure — synthesized in the browser from a parsed GFF."
  wide
>
  <article class="prose">
    <h1>JBrowse integration</h1>
    <p>
      Type any human gene to build a connected JBrowse session: a
      collapsed-intron genome view, its 100-way protein alignment, and the
      AlphaFold structure.
    </p>

    <details>
      <summary>How this works</summary>
      <p>
        The page resolves the gene to its canonical (MANE / RefSeq Select)
        transcript and parses the GFF in your browser. There is no
        <code>collapseIntrons</code> option in JBrowse — the trick is to give the
        Linear Genome View a <code>loc</code> made of the exon ranges,
        space-separated, so each renders back-to-back and the introns disappear.
        Everything is computed live from public data (mygene.info, the UCSC
        RefSeq Select GFF over tabix, AlphaFold); only the alignment slice comes
        from a hosted file.
      </p>
    </details>

    <GeneExplorer client:only="react" />
  </article>
</Base>
